    <description><![CDATA[<div class="featured-image">
                <img src="/images/posts/intro_numpy.webp" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
            </div><h1 id="intro-to-numpy" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#intro-to-numpy" class="header-mark"></a>Intro to Numpy</h1><p>There are many notebooks out there that cover some of these subjects, including Numpy&rsquo;s <a href="https://numpy.org/doc/stable/user/absolute_beginners.html#" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">quickstart</a>.</p>
<p>I am using this notebook to gather the most important and maybe not so important parts of this library, which will depend on what you are using it for.</p>
<h2 id="why-numpy" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#why-numpy" class="header-mark"></a>Why numpy?</h2><p>Well numpy is used in many mathematical computations due to its blazing fast calculations speeds.</p>
<p>The reason its so fast is due to the vectoriszation of matrices which calculations are done through pre-compiled C code.</p>]]></description>
